#############################################################################
### Descripton of the column (parameter) labels ###
##ReadPair1: Filename (without location) for the fastq reads pair 1
##ReadPair2: Filename (without location) for the fastq reads pair 2
##AmpliconCutSites: Filename (without location) for the tab-seperated text
##	containing each amplicon name and it's nucleotide cut site for the sample
##	(/barcode) for example: R38_tar	115

##Following options if specified on the command line, will take precedence
##	over all the values in all the entries in the configuration data below.

##ReferenceSeqFile: Filename (without location) for the reference sequences
##	per sample (/barcode).

##Following 4 paramters are used for adapter trimming:
##AvgReadLength: Estimate of average read length, single pair (trim by length)
##MinAmpliconLength: Minimum amplicon length (overall/per sample) (trimm by length)
##ForwardAdapter: Sequence of the forward adapter, (trim by sequence)
##ReverseAdapter: Sequence of the reverse adapter, (trim by sequence)
